#compdef intercept
# =============================================================================
# intercept — XFHG's "INTERCEPT - DevSecOps toolkit" — a Go
#             CLI for "Policy as Code Auditing" that loads YAML/
#             JSON/TOML/INI policy files and runs parallelized
#             audits combining ripgrep pattern matching, OPA
#             Rego evaluation, goss compliance checks, and
#             remote SSH execution against fleets of hosts.
#             Distinguishing from conftest, opa, regula, terrascan,
#             checkov, kubescape, and other policy-as-code
#             scanners by:
#               - 5 ROOT SUBCOMMANDS via cobra:
#                   * audit              — optimized parallelized
#                                          audit through all loaded
#                                          policies
#                   * observe            — schedule + path-monitor
#                                          based realtime policy
#                                          triggering
#                   * sys                — test embedded core
#                                          binaries (rg + goss)
#                   * remote             — execute remote ops via
#                                          embedded gossh (run /
#                                          push / fetch / script)
#                   * version            — print build info
#               - 4 REMOTE OPS via `intercept remote`:
#                   * run [HOST...]      — execute commands on
#                                          target hosts
#                   * push [HOST...]     — copy local files +
#                                          dirs to target hosts
#                   * fetch [HOST...]    — copy files from target
#                                          hosts to local
#                   * script [HOST...]   — execute local shell
#                                          script on target hosts
#               - EMBEDDED ripgrep + goss + gossh BINARIES per-
#                 platform (Darwin amd64/arm64, Linux amd64/
#                 arm32/arm64, Windows amd64) — intercept ships
#                 with binary-embedded rg / goss / gossh via
#                 platform-specific embed_*.go files, extracts
#                 them at runtime to a temp dir, no external
#                 dependencies required
#               - SARIF + LOG OUTPUT MATRICES — output-type flag
#                 accepts comma-separated list "SARIF,LOG"; log-
#                 type accepts "MINIMAL,RESULTS,POLICY,REPORT"
#                 — multiple output forms generated per run
#               - 4 POLICY TYPES — scan (ripgrep regex), assure
#                 (presence assertions), runtime (goss runtime
#                 compliance), rego (OPA policy) — single policy
#                 file can mix types
#               - 4 CONFIG FORMATS — YAML / JSON / TOML / INI
#                 policy files parsed via type_yaml.go /
#                 type_json.go / type_toml.go / type_ini.go
#               - SCHEDULE + PATH-MONITORING WATCH MODE — observe
#                 subcommand uses fsnotify-style path monitoring
#                 + cron schedules to trigger policies in real
#                 time (file modification events / time-based)
#               - KSUID RUN ID — every run gets unique ksuid
#                 (K-Sortable Unique ID) identifier for tracking
#                 results across runs
#               - ZEROLOG STRUCTURED LOGGING via 4 logger
#                 channels (mlog/flog/plog/rlog) for minimal /
#                 file / policy / report log streams
#               - HTTP API DISPATCH via go-resty/resty — when
#                 policies define remote URL targets, intercept
#                 uses resty to POST audit results / GET remote
#                 policy bundles / etc.
#             Used by: security engineering teams writing custom
#             compliance policies, DevSecOps pipelines auditing
#             infrastructure-as-code repos pre-merge, and as a
#             reference implementation of go-resty/resty +
#             cobra + zerolog + ksuid + embedded-binary composition
#             in Go.
#
