#          (cobra is documented across hundreds of Go completions;
#          resty is the new variant being documented here,
#          expanding Axis 16 — HTTP Clients — to Go).
# Library: github.com/go-resty/resty/v2 v2.14.0
#          (resty — "Simple HTTP, REST, and SSE client library
#           for Go" — Mathew Roy + 200+ contributors.
#           Distinct from reqwest (R649, Rust Axis 16 opener)
#           and from Go's net/http stdlib by being:
#              1. FLUENT BUILDER API — resty.New().R() returns
#                 a Request builder that chains setters fluently:
#                   client := resty.New()
#                   resp, err := client.R().
#                       SetHeader("Authorization", "Bearer " + token).
#                       SetQueryParam("page", "2").
#                       SetBody(&Payload{Foo: "bar"}).
#                       SetResult(&Result{}).
#                       Post("https://api.example.com/users")
#                 Stdlib net/http requires manual http.NewRequest
#                 + req.Header.Set + bytes.NewBuffer body
#                 marshaling for every request.
#              2. AUTOMATIC JSON / XML SERIALIZATION — SetBody
#                 accepts a struct; resty marshals to JSON (or
#                 XML based on Content-Type) automatically.
#                 SetResult accepts a struct pointer; resty
#                 unmarshals response body into it:
#                   type User struct { ID int; Name string }
#                   var u User
#                   client.R().SetResult(&u).Get(url)
#                   // u populated from response JSON
#                 Stdlib net/http requires manual
#                 json.NewEncoder/Decoder.
#              3. RETRY WITH BACKOFF — built-in retry strategies
#                 (constant / exponential / custom) via
#                 client.SetRetryCount + SetRetryWaitTime +
#                 SetRetryMaxWaitTime + AddRetryCondition.
#                 Stdlib net/http has no retry built-in (manual
#                 loops required).
#              4. MIDDLEWARE HOOKS — OnBeforeRequest +
#                 OnAfterResponse + OnError + OnSuccess +
#                 OnInvalid hooks for logging, metrics, auth
#                 refresh, etc.  Stdlib net/http requires
#                 manual RoundTripper wrappers.
#              5. PROXY + TLS CONFIG via simple setters —
#                 client.SetProxy("http://proxy:8080"),
#                 client.SetTLSClientConfig(&tls.Config{...}).
#              6. AUTH HELPERS — SetBasicAuth, SetAuthToken,
#                 SetAuthScheme for first-class HTTP auth
#                 patterns.
#              7. FILE UPLOAD HELPERS — SetFile, SetFiles,
#                 SetMultipartFormData for multipart/form-data
#                 uploads.
#              8. CONTEXT-AWARE — SetContext for context
#                 cancellation / timeout propagation through
#                 request lifecycle.
#              9. DEBUG MODE — SetDebug(true) prints full
#                 request + response to stdout (curl-style)
#                 for debugging.
#             10. MATHEW-ROY / GO-RESTY ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE —
#                 Mathew Roy maintains the go-resty organization
#                 with 200+ contributors; resty is the foundational
#                 HTTP client used by Drone CI, Skuid, K3s,
#                 Crossplane, Pulumi Go SDK, GitLab CLI, and
