# (resty THIS — Axis 16 expands to 2 variants) → expected R651
# TS-Node=70 → R652 95th language.  This is the 2nd of 3 leader
# bumps in the current segment.
#
# This completion EXPANDS Axis 16 (HTTP CLIENTS) to TWO documented
# variants — symmetrically distributed across Rust (reqwest R649)
# and Go (resty THIS R650).  TS-Node Axis 16 variant expected in
# R651 to complete three-language symmetry.
#
#   Axis 16 (HTTP CLIENTS) variants:
#     - reqwest (seanmonstar/reqwest) — R649 (_rustormy) — Rust
#       ASYNC + BLOCKING dual HTTP client; built on hyper;
#       rustls/native-tls; serde JSON; Sean McArthur / Hyperium
#     - resty (go-resty/resty) — R650 (THIS) — Go FLUENT BUILDER
#       API; automatic JSON/XML serialization; retry + middleware
#       hooks; Mathew Roy / go-resty ecosystem
#
# Two Axis 16 variants address DIFFERENT design emphases:
#   reqwest            = ASYNC + BLOCKING dual + serde integration
#                         (Rust)
#   resty              = FLUENT BUILDER + auto JSON/XML + retry +
#                         middleware (Go)
